com.opengamma.strata.product

Interface SecurityTrade<P extends Product>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type of the product
    All Superinterfaces:
    CalculationTarget, FinanceTrade, LinkResolvable<SecurityTrade<P>>, Trade
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BondFutureOptionTrade, BondFutureTrade, DeliverableSwapFutureTrade, EquityTrade, FixedCouponBondTrade, GenericFutureOptionTrade, GenericFutureTrade, IborFutureOptionTrade, IborFutureTrade

    public interface SecurityTrade<P extends Product>
extends FinanceTrade, LinkResolvable<SecurityTrade<P>>
    A trade that is directly based on a security.

    A security trade is a Trade that contains a reference to a Security. The security is held via a SecurityLink, which allows for the security to be managed as reference data, separately from the trade.

    Implementations of this interface must be immutable beans.

    • Method Detail

      • getSecurityLink

        SecurityLink<P> getSecurityLink()
        Gets the link to the security that was traded.

        A security link provides loose coupling between different parts of the object model. For example, this allows the trade to be stored in a different database to the security.

        A link can be in one of two states, resolvable and resolved. In the resolvable state, the link contains the identifier and product type of the security. In the resolved state, the link directly embeds the security.

        When the link is in the resolvable state, the getSecurity() AND getProduct() methods will throw an IllegalStateException.

        To ensure that the link is resolved, call resolveLinks(LinkResolver).

        Returns:
        the link to the security, which may be in either the resolvable or resolved state

      • getSecurity

        default Security<P> getSecurity()
        Gets the security that was traded, throwing an exception if not resolved.

        Returns the underlying security that was traded. This is obtained from getSecurityLink().

        The link has two states, resolvable and resolved. The security can only be returned if the link is resolved. If the link is in the resolvable state, this method will throw an IllegalStateException.

        To ensure that the link is resolved, call resolveLinks(LinkResolver).

        Returns:
        full details of the security
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the security link is not resolved

      • getProduct

        default P getProduct()
        Gets the underlying product that was agreed when the trade occurred, throwing an exception if not resolved.

        Returns the underlying product that captures the contracted financial details of the trade. This is obtained from getSecurityLink().

        The link has two states, resolvable and resolved. The product can only be returned if the link is resolved. If the link is in the resolvable state, this method will throw an IllegalStateException.

        To ensure that the link is resolved, call resolveLinks(LinkResolver).

        Returns:
        the product
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the security link is not resolved

      • resolveLinks

        SecurityTrade<P> resolveLinks(LinkResolver resolver)
        Returns a trade where all links have been resolved.

        This method examines the trade, locates any links and resolves them. The result is fully resolved with all data available for use. Calling getSecurity() or getProduct() on the result will not throw an exception.

        An exception is thrown if a link cannot be resolved.

        Specified by:
        resolveLinks in interface LinkResolvable<SecurityTrade<P extends Product>>
        Parameters:
        resolver - the resolver to use
        Returns:
        the fully resolved trade
        Throws:
        LinkResolutionException - if a link cannot be resolved
